From the “standard average” analysis and co-localisation of γ-H2AX foci with 53BP1 we assigned the patient's repair status as close-to-normal. However, analysis of “principal average”, foci per cell frequency distributions and survival curves challenged this initial conclusion.

These studies indicate new dimensions of the γ-H2AX assay that, with further elaboration and exemplification, have the potential to augment its power to predict radiosensitivity.},
